[2] USA - South Dakota
Date: 5 Jul 2011
Source: South Dakota Animal Industry Board [edited]
http://aib.sd.gov/News/PDF%20Files/2011.4.14%20Anthrax%20News%20Release.pdf



Anthrax vaccination reminder
----------------------------
State veterinarian Dr Dustin Oedekoven reminds livestock producers to
remain diligent in vaccinating their livestock against anthrax.
Flooding in various parts of the state has created conditions that are
favorable for Anthrax. Anthrax spores may lie dormant in soil for
years, only to surface after flooding. The most effective way to
manage the disease is through annual preventive vaccination, as
unvaccinated animals tend to die suddenly after exposure, with no
opportunity for treatment. Your local veterinarian is a valuable
source of information regarding vaccination protocols.

[For further information, go to
http://aib.sd.gov/diseasecontrol.shtm#cattle]

--
communicated by:
Dustin Oedekoven, DVM
State Veterinarian
